{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Dhiman and Vishwakarma (2019) collect methods on abnormal human activity detectors both in 2D and 3D domains.",
    "The authors claim that autoencoder-based human activity detectors are sensitive to variations in the view.",
    "The goal of the autoencoder is to recreate the original data; therefore, the metric used compares the input data with the output data, calculating the difference between them.",
    "This metric is called reconstruction loss (1), and in most cases mean squared error is used:",
    "where x is the input data, ′ is the reconstructed data, z is the latent space, e(⋅) is the encoder and d(⋅) is the decoder."
  ]
}